Rambo said he thinks that could be a good spot for the club to restructure its academy.

Aberulance and his coaching staff and staff from other former clubs saw a chance to get themselves into the Top 20 and to do so will depend upon the success of the new team.

"We have taken the club off the map, but we've got no shortage of places to work within that. We'll talk to the players and they'll decide if we can bring in a few players that would be better suited for football," he said.
